main event: An elliptical silver object was observed in Teddington, England, on 1 September 1955, during a smooth gradual descent.
interesting points: The observation lasted 4-5 minutes,The object was reflecting the sun,The observer described the object as having no erratic movements,The observer lost sight of the object while driving through a wooded area,The investigation concluded that there was insufficient data for evaluation.
witness description: Miss [REDACTED], age 39, seamstress. Observer noted wearing Polaroid sunglasses.
